    "text": "Taxation of Minor Children Simplification Act of 2004 - Amends the Internal Revenue Code to revise rules for the taxation of the income of minor children (under age 14). Repeals the allocable parental tax rules. Allows parents to elect to claim the child's gross income and deductions on the parents' tax return."
